%BOM---------------------
Date:4/19/2012 12:05:47 AM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
I read the "non advertised" DELL writeup on SA. It is detailed, but I don't
think it offers much new insight. As I mentioned before, I hold some DELL and I
might buy more.

IMHO, the real question in tech space is not whether DELL is a buy or INTC is a
buy or MSFT is a buy. The real questions are two: how much money to put into
tech space and what company (or companies) to overweigh. Easiest choice is
"some money" and "mostly equal shares", but this is somewhat a copout.

I would be really interested if somebody gave a good argument why one of the
above (or another company like AAPL, GOOG, IBM, STX, SNDK, ORCL, HPQ...) is a
big overweigh vs all the others.

Personally I have MSFT on overweigh, but I don't claim that I have a very
strong argument for it. IMHO, it has potentially highest moat while also having
low valuation. However, it's not a strong argument, since other companies may
have comparable or stronger moats while having a better growth or lower
valuation. Some other companies might also be buyout candidates, while MSFT
isn't.

I believe someone on this thread claimed that HPQ is a best bet in tech space.
I did not find that claim convincing. But that's just me. :)

Overall, I find that making comparative judgement is very tricky and hard.

Disclaimer: I own positions in DELL, INTC, MSFT, SNDK.
%EOM----------------------

