margin-of-safety. However, IF the company could maintain its current very good
profit margins and ROE (which the company has not been able to do in past),
then the stock should do okay. Seems to have plenty of cash and negligible ltd,
so that helps.

I'll go for a few shares here for a spec. While HITK does fall into my value
box on it's current good numbers, its history is not so encouraging.

