Date:4/23/2012 3:08:06 PM
From:Sergio H
Did you look into SGT's long term agreements? SGT's LTAs have increased
dramatically. Price on LTAs benefits their customers and SGT can better plan on
production to meet demand. But what happens if prices drop significantly and
customers walk away? SGT ends up with a huge backlog and further deprecess
product price. I see this as inevitable given that the shortage created by the
Thailand floods will eventually be resolved.

I think that the Alpha site is fantastic for what you get. Sure there's some
not so good stuff, but there's a bunch of gems. It always comes down to doing
your own research anyway.

You can access info pretty quickly at the site and then decide what you want to
read....

Say you're looking into Graham Number:

http://seekingalpha.com/search/?source=search_general&q=graham+number&cx=001514
37567335583750%3Acdhc2yeo2ko&cof=FORID%3A11%3BNB%3A1&goto_search_tab=

Or how about some value plays:

http://seekingalpha.com/search/?source=search_general&q=value+stocks&cx=0015142
7567335583750%3Acdhc2yeo2ko&cof=FORID%3A11%3BNB%3A1&goto_search_tab=

Or you want to learn about BDCs:

http://seekingalpha.com/search/?source=search_general&q=business+development+co
panies&cx=001514237567335583750%3Acdhc2yeo2ko&cof=FORID%3A11%3BNB%3A1&goto_sear
h_tab=general

There's some authors that I have tagged and I like the availability of
conference calls including the q and a. And its all free. I take a look at the
Alpha site when I am looking for new ideas or want to see what others are
thinking when I find something I am interested in.

Thanks for sharing your ideas.
